
Building Your First App
http://developer.android.com/training/basics/firstapp/index.html


Command Line
==============

Create a project:

  android list targets

  android create project --target <target-id> --name MyFirstApp \
  --path <path-to-workspace>/MyFirstApp --activity MainActivity \
  --package com.example.myfirstapp

Do this from the root directory of the project:

  ant debug

Install:

  adb install bin/MyFirstApp-debug.apk

Launch emulator manager:

  android avd


Source Files to be used as a project
======================================

All these source files can be imported into an android project with 
existing source code. But it needs also the libs/android-support-v4.jar 
to be placed in the new project directory. The jar can be found at 
adt.../sdk/extras/android/support/v4/.


